(16, 'cm-21-20', 5, 'Inner Peace Gel', '', 'Penetrating wild yam gel for menopause ', '<p class=\\"MsoNoSpacing\\">Inner Peace Gel is a topical formulation manufactured with natural ingredients that contain diosgenin, a naturally occurring steroid which helps reduce the symptoms associated to post-menstrual syndrome and menopause.</p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNoSpacing\\"><strong>Key Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Contains diosgenin, which when applied topically, helps reduce inflammation, relaxes the muscles. Also useful in promoting bone health and controlling endometriosis</li>\n<li>Utilizes superior water-based delivery system that provides 2x the amount of&nbsp;diogenin delivered by conventional wild yam creams</li>\n<li>Glides on smooth, no sticky residue in the skin after application</li>\n</ul>', '<div>Inner Peace Gel is a topical treatment formulated to help alleviate symptoms of P.M.S. and</div>\n<div>\n<div>menopause. It contains diosgenin, the scientifically recognized active ingredient in Wild Yam.</div>\n<div>Diosgenin is absorbed well through the skin, especially on the soft tissue areas such as</div>\n</div>\n<div>the breasts or inner arms. Diosgenin intake via the skin interacts with progesterone receptors, and nourishes the female glandular system to alleviate symptoms associated with lowered receptors. Superior water-based delivery system provides 2.4 mg of diogenin per ml, almost&nbsp;<strong>twice&nbsp;</strong>as much<strong>&nbsp;</strong>as<strong>&nbsp;</strong>the amount of diogenin delivered by conventional wild yam creams.</div>\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div>', '<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Ingredients: </span>Purified water; 8% Extract of Wild Yam; 2% Extract of</div>\n<div>\n<div>Chaste Berry Tree; 2% Extract of Chamomile; 2% Tocopheryl Acetate;</div>\n<div>Carbomer, Triethanolamine, Phenoxyethanol, Grapefruit seed extract.</div>\n</div>', '<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use</span> (Adults): Twice daily, massage 1 to 2 teaspoon</div>\n<div>\n<div>of gel on the neck, wrists, breasts or inner arms. For optimum</div>\n<div>absorption, vary application area. Keep out of reach of children.</div>\n<div>Store in a cool, dry place to preserve freshness.</div>\n</div>', '', '', 'Gel Inner Peace', '', '', '', '<p>Le Gel Inner Peace fait partie du Programme oral et topique Inner Balance. Un traitement topique con&ccedil;u pour att&eacute;nuer les sympt&ocirc;mes du syndrome pr&eacute;menstruel et ceux de la m&eacute;nopause. Ce gel contient 8% d\\''extrait d\\''igname sauvage mexicain, 2% d\\''extrait de vitex et 2 % d\\''extrait de camomille, et il contient la plus grande quantit&eacute; qui soit de diosg&eacute;nine naturelle. Le syst&egrave;me de livraison &agrave; base d\\''eau sup&eacute;rieur du Gel Inner Peace fournit 2,4 mg de diosg&eacute;nine par millilitre, soit presque 2 fois la quantit&eacute; contenue dans les cr&egrave;mes d\\''igname sauvage conventionnelles, et ceci, sans laisser de r&eacute;sidu collant. L\\''apport de diosg&eacute;nine via la peau interagit avec les r&eacute;cepteurs de progest&eacute;rone, et nourrit le syst&egrave;me glandulaire femelle pour all&eacute;ger les sympt&ocirc;mes associ&eacute;s aux r&eacute;cepteurs r&eacute;duits. Le gel aide aussi &agrave; r&eacute;duire l\\''inflammation, d&eacute;tend les muscles, et semble &ecirc;tre utile pour promouvoir la sant&eacute; osseuse et pour contr&ocirc;ler l\\''endom&eacute;triose.</p>', '', '', '', '', 8, 'No', '', '', 'Active'),
(17, 'sp-20-02', 2, 'Milk Thistle (Silymarin)', '', 'Helps support liver function', '<div>The liver is a key organ used in the detoxifying process. &nbsp;Milk thistle (silymarin)&nbsp;has shown positive benefits in supporting and protecting the liver while enhancing the overall detoxification processes.</div>\n<div>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Substances in milk thistle protect the liver from toxins, including certain drugs such as acetaminophen (eg. Tylenol), which can cause liver damage in high doses</li>\n<li>Also has antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which may help the liver repair itself by growing new cells</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<p><strong><span style=\\"font-family: ArialNarrow-Bold; font-size: xx-small;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: ArialNarrow-Bold; font-size: xx-small;\\"> </span></span></strong></p>\n<div><strong>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 18pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\\">&nbsp;</p>\n</strong></div>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>', '<p>Our bodies incur toxin accumulation on a daily basis, to levels that can be dangerous to overall health. &nbsp;The human body does have the potential to naturally eliminate these toxins through various organs like the liver, kidney, stomach, intestines, lungs and skin (also collectively known as &nbsp;emunctories). Milk thistle (silymarin)&nbsp;has shown positive benefits in supporting and protecting the liver and enhancing the detox process and waste filtration processes. &nbsp;Milk thistle (silymarin) is a flowering herb related to the daisy and ragweed family. It is native to Mediterranean countries.</p>\n<p>Source:</p>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/herb/milk-thistle#ixzz2oz6zALcc\\">Milk thistle | University of Maryland Medical Center</a>&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/herb/milk-thistle#ixzz2oz6zALcc\\">http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/herb/milk-thistle#ixzz2oz6zALcc</a>&nbsp;</li>\n<li>NHPD Monograph on Milk Thistle. June 2009.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', '<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal ingredients:</span> Each capsule contains:</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Milk Thistle (Silybum marianum) fruit</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">(Standardized to 80% Silymarin) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.......................................................150 mg</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Providing: Silymarin &hellip;&hellip;..&hellip;&hellip;....................................................................120 mg</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Dandelion Root (Taraxacum officinale) root ....................................................100 mg</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Alfalfa (Medicago sativa) herb top ...................................................................100 mg</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-fam