(24, 'sp0143', 4, 'Vitamin K2', '', 'Essential for maximum calcium utilization', '<p>Vitamin K2 is required in order to use calcium in the process of creating a healthy bone matrix-it activates a protein called osteocalcin, which is involved in the bone-building process (it binds calcium to the bone, thus strengthening the skeleton). Vitamin K deficiency leads to inactive osteocalcin that cannot bind calcium to the surface of the bone.</p>', '<p>Higher levels of vitamin K2 are strongly associated with better bone mass, better bone density, improved bone geometry and improved mineral content. Strong bones developed in childhood - and maintained afterward - reduce the risk of osteoporotic fracture as high peak bone mass acts as a buffer against the bone loss we all experience later in life.  Unfortunately, the majority of adults and children are vitamin K deficient. In recent years the dietary intake of K vitamins has dramatically declined. Therefore, supplementation with natural vitamin K2 is highly recommended.  The most potent form of vitamin K2 is a subclass called MK-7. It is so potent that it is only needed in microgram amounts. MK-4 (another form of K2) has also been shown to be beneficial for bone, but is less potent (requiring larger doses) and is also cleared from the body rapidly.  Inno-Vite\\''s Vitamin K2 offers the safest and the most effective form of this amazing vitamin.</p>', '<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Medicinal Ingredients: Each vegetarian capsule contains:</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Vitamin K2 (MK-7 from Bacillus subtilis natto)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.............