: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Cautions: Do not use if the seal is broken.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>', '', '', 'UTI Protect ', '', '', '', '<p>Alors que le Escherichia coli (ou  E. coli) est une bact&eacute;rie qui se trouve normalement dans les voies intestinales, celle-ci peut avoir un effet perturbateur sur la sant&eacute; en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral si elle se trouve l&agrave; o&ugrave; elle ne devrait pas. En fait, 80 &agrave; 90% de toutes les infections de la vessie (cystite) et des infections des voies urinaires sont caus&eacute;es par le E. coli qui envahit les voies urinaires; le taux d\\''infection est 50 fois plus &eacute;lev&eacute; chez les femmes et les jeunes filles que chez les hommes.<br /> La bact&eacute;rie E. coli peut aussi se trouver dans le vagin et migrer vers l\\''ur&egrave;tre puis jusque dans la vessie, ce qui fait que de nombreuses femmes se retrouvent avec une infection de la vessie, surtout apr&egrave;s des relations sexuelles.<br /> Sympt&ocirc;mes d\\''infections de la vessie et des voies urinaires <br /> Une vari&eacute;t&eacute; de sympt&ocirc;mes peuvent indiquer la pr&eacute;sence d\\''une infection des voies urinaires ou de la vessie, et le degr&eacute; de s&eacute;v&eacute;rit&eacute; de ces sympt&ocirc;mes peut varier de l&eacute;ger &agrave; grave et m&ecirc;me extr&ecirc;mement grave dans certains cas. Parmi les sympt&ocirc;mes courants, on retrouve:<br /> &bull; une sensation de brulure au moment d\\''uriner; <br /> &bull; un sentiment persistant d\\''avoir besoin d\\''uriner sans pouvoir se vider compl&egrave;tement; <br /> &bull; des urines ros&eacute;es ou rouge&acirc;tres, ou troubles; <br /> &bull; une urine qui d&eacute;gage une odeur naus&eacute;abonde; <br /> &bull; une douleur ou une pression dans le bas-ventre; <br /> &bull; des mictions fr&eacute;quentes.<br /> UTI Protect d\\''Inno-Vite <br /> <strong>Ce que fait UTI Protect :</strong> <br /> traite et pr&eacute;vient les cystites et les infections urinaires r&eacute;currentes en inhibant l\\''habilet&eacute; de la bact&eacute;rie E. coli&rsquo; &agrave; adh&eacute;rer aux parois de la vessie et des voies urinaires;<br /> agit comme diur&eacute;tique pour rincer la vessie et les voies urinaires;<br /> r&eacute;duit la d&eacute;pendance aux antibiotiques.</p>', '', '', '', '', 13, 'No', '', '80031854', 'Active'),
(31, 'sb10193', 4, 'Inno-Osteo', '', 'Complete Nutritional Support for Superior Bone Health', '<p>Bone is a living, growing tissue. It is made mostly of collagen, a protein that provides a soft framework, and calcium phosphate, a mineral that adds strength and hardens the framework. This combination of collagen and calcium makes our bones both flexible and strong, which in turn help them to withstand stress. So the key is to create dense, but flexible bones, and this is why Inno-Osteo focuses on both collagen formation and the minerals that bind to collagen to create strength and density.  Inno-Osteo contains calcium and all other key bone health nutrients in research-backed doses and forms.</p>', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Per softgel:</h1>\n<table width=\\"100%\\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Calcium(citrate,phosphate,carbonate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">200 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Magnesium (citrate, oxide)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">83.33 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Phosphorus (calcium phosphate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">50 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Silicon (colloidal silicon dioxide)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">5 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Zinc (gluconate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">1.67 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Boron (citrate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">0.5 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Copper (citrate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">0.17 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manganese (ascorbate)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">0.17 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin C</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">30 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin D3</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">(166.67 IU) 4.17 mcg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin K2 (MK-7)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">7.5 mcg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin B6</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">2 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Folic acid</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">30 mcg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin B12 (methyl)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">30 mcg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>HMR (as HMRlignan)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">8.33 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>l-Lysine</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">166.67 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>l-Proline</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">50 mg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Betaine HCl</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">10 mg</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 10, 'No', '', 'NPN#12345667', 'Disable'),
(32, 'sb10197', 4, 'Vitamin K2 Drops with Vitamin D3', '', 'Helps prevent Vitamin K deficiency', '<p>Formulation includes Vitamin K2 from &nbsp;MK-7, the only Canadian vitamin K2 free from the syntetic anti-foaming chemical, dimethyl polysiloxane. &nbsp;Higher levels of Vitamin K are strongly associated with better bone mass, heavier bone density, improved bone geometry and overall mineral content because it activates a special protein called osteocalcin that works synergistically with &nbsp;calcium to build healthy bone tissue. Strong bones developed in childhood and maintained in adulthood reduce the risk of osteoporotic fractures.&nbsp;Vitamin D is also vital to strong bones and teeth and help with overall calcium absorption.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\\"bold\\">Safest and most effective form of Vitamin K2: </span>Formulated with MK-7, which helps improve activation of osteocalcin.</li>\n<li><span class=\\"bold\\">Increase calcium absorption potential: </span>includes vitamin D3.</li>\n<li><span class=\\"bold\\">Improves blood stability: </span>Vitamin K2 provides longer blood half-life.</li>\n</ul>', '<p>Specific forms of K2, like MK-7, have a very long half life in</p>\n<p>circulation, giving the body a steady supply of vitamin K2 24 hours a day.</p>\n<p>Innovite Health\\''s Vitamin K2 contains natural Vitamin K2 in its most</p>\n<p>absorbable form to promote optimum bone health and it is the only MK-7</p>\n<p>product in Canada free from the synthetic anti-foaming chemical, dimethyl</p>\n<p>polysiloxane.</p>\n<p>Vitamin K2 is vital in supporting bone health &nbsp;Inno-Vite\\''s Vitamin K2 Drops contains contains the safest and the most effective form of Vitamin K2 as MK-7 and has been shown to be the optimal vitamin K2 product with longer blood half-life (resulting in more stable blood levels) and better effect on bone and cardiovascular health through the activation of osteocalcin and MGP</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Better effect on bone and cardiovascular health through the activation of osteocalcin and MGP</li>\n<li>MGP&nbsp; is the most potent inhibitor of soft tissue calcification currently known. When activated by vitamin K, MGP prevents calcium from building up in the arteries</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vitamin K is required in order to use calcium in the process of creating a</p>\n<p>healthy bone matrix. It activates a protein called &ldquo;osteocalcin&rdquo;, which is</p>\n<p>involved in the bone-building process. Osteocalcin binds calcium to the</p>\n<p>bone, thus strengthening the skeleton. Insufficient vitamin K leads to inactive</p>\n<p>osteocalcin that cannot bind calcium to the surface of the bone.</p>\n<p>Higher levels of Vitamin K are strongly associated with better bone mass,</p>\n<p>better bone density, improved bone geometry and improved mineral</p>\n<p>content. Strong bones developed in childhood and maintained in adulthood</p>\n<p>reduce the risk of osteoporotic fractures.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the same time, vitamin K activates another protein called MGP &ndash; the most</p>\n<p>potent inhibitor of soft tissue calcification currently known. When activated</p>\n<p>by vitamin K, MGP prevents calcium from building up in the arteries.</p>\n<p>Two naturally-occurring forms of vitamin K have been identified, and these</p>\n<p>are designated as vitamin K1 and K2. Natural Vitamin K2 is the source of</p>\n<p>vitamin K preferred by all tissues including cartilage, bone and soft tissues.</p>', '<h2>Medicinal Ingredients:</h2>\n<p>Each drop (0.05 mL) contains:</p>\n<table width=\\"100%\\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin K2 (MK-7 from Bacillus subtilis natto)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">5 mcg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol)</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">0.625 mcg (25 IU)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Non-Medicinal Ingredients:</h2>\n<p>Grape seed oil.</p>\n<h2>Directions for use:</h2>\n<p>Take this product with food for best absorption, or as directed by a healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<table width=\\"100%\\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Children (1-3 years old):</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">5-6 drops daily</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Children (4-8 years old):</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">6-11 drops daily</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adolescents (9-13) years old:</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">9-12 drops daily</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adolescents 14-18 years old:</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">9-15 drops daily.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adults (19 years and older):</td>\n<td align=\\"right\\">9-24 drops daily.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'No', '', '80021003', 'Active'),
(33, 'sb10198', 4, 'Vitamin D3 drops with Vitamin K2', '', 'Helps Prevent Vitamin D Deficiency', '<p>Extensive research on vitamin D has confirmed its importance in the absorption and use of calcium and phosphorus; also in maintaining a healthy immune, nervous and cardiovascular systems, cognitive function and emotional well-being.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Formulated with cholecalciferol the most desirable form of Vitamin D3</li>\n<li>&nbsp;2.5 mcg of Vitamin K2 per drop promotes the construction of healthy bones</li>\n<li>Vitamin K2 from &nbsp;MK-7, the only Canadian vitamin K2 free from the synthetic anti-foaming chemical</li>\n</ul>', '<p>Vitamin D is vital to strong bones, teeth and a healthy immune system. It&rsquo;s also called the</p>\n<p>&ldquo;sunshine vitamin&rdquo; because it&rsquo;s produced in your skin in response to sunlight. Vitamin D3 is a</p>\n<p>fat-soluble vitamin that can affect as many as 2,000 genes in the body with several important</p>\n<p>functions. Perhaps the most vital are regulating the absorption of calcium and phosphorous from</p>\n<p>the intestines, and facilitating normal immune system function.</p>\n<p>Getting a sufficient amount of this vitamin is important for normal growth and development of</p>\n<p>bones and teeth, as well as improved resistance against certain diseases. If your body doesn&rsquo;t</p>\n<p>get enough vitamin D, you&rsquo;re at risk of developing bone abnormalities such as osteomalacia (soft</p>\n<p>bones) or osteoporosis (fragile bones). However, getting enough from sun exposure has</p>\n<p>become challenging as people cover-up when going outside in the summer or wear sunblock to</p>\n<p>minimize the harmful effects of excessive sun exposure. Since most food is a poor source of</p>\n<p>vitamin D, supplementation is not only ideal, but in most cases, absolutely essential.</p>\n<p>Recommended Vitamin D3 intake by The Institute of Medicine (IOM):</p>\n<p>&bull; children and teens: 600 IU</p>\n<p>&bull; adults up to age 70: 600 IU</p>\n<p>&bull; adults over age 70: 800 IU</p>\n<p>&bull; pregnant or breastfeeding women: 600 IU</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>New research is showing most people do not consume enough vitamin K2, which</p>\n<p>helps our body manage where to send that calcium (we want it in the bones, not arteries or soft</p>\n<p>tissues). Hence this &nbsp;Liquid D3 is the only vitamin D supplement on the Canadian</p>\n<p>market that contains a small amount of vitamin K2 (as MK-7).&nbsp;Formulation includes Vitamin K2 from &nbsp;MK-7, the only Canadian vitamin K2 free from the synthetic anti-foaming chemical, dimethyl polysiloxane. &nbsp;Higher levels of Vitamin K are strongly associated with better bone mass, heavier bone density, improved bone geometry and overall mineral content because it activates a special protein called osteocalcin that works synergistically with &nbsp;calcium to build healthy bone tissue.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\\"font-size: 7.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\\"><br /></span></p>', '<h2><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Medicinal Ingredients: Each drop (0.05 mL) contains:</span></span></p>\n<span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol)......................12.5 mcg (500 IU)</span></span></p>\n<span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Vitamin K2 (MK-7 from Bacillus subt