 I, Burton-Freeman B, Tissa Kappagoda C. Mechanism of the endothelium-dependent relaxation evoked by a grape seed extract. Clin Sci (Lond). 2008 Feb;114(4):331-7.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.lifescienceglobal.com/home/cart?view=product&amp;id=241\\" target=\\"_blank\\"><span style=\\"mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB;\\" lang=\\"EN-GB\\">M. Robinson, et al. <strong><span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\\">Effect of Grape Seed Extract on Blood Pressure in Subjects with Pre-Hypertension. J Pharm Nut Sci. 2013 :155-159.</span></strong><strong><span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; font-weight: normal; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.nature.com/ejcn/journal/v56/n11/full/1601464a.html\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Hodgson JM, et al. Coenzyme Q10 improves blood pressure and glycaemic  control: a controlled trial in subjects with type 2 diabetes. Eur J Clin  Nutr. 2002 Nov;56(11):1137-42.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://ajcn.nutrition.org/content/early/2012/05/02/ajcn.111.029330.abstract\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Ellinger S, et al. Epicatechin ingested via cocoa products reduces blood  pressure in humans: a nonlinear regression model with a Bayesian  approach. Am J Clin Nutr. 2012 Jun;95(6):1365-77. Epub 2012 May 2.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://hyper.ahajournals.org/content/60/3/794.long\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Desideri G, et al. Benefits in cognitive function, blood pressure, and  insulin resistance through cocoa flavanol consumption in elderly  subjects with mild cognitive impairment: the Cocoa, Cognition, and Aging  (CoCoA) study. Hypertension. 2012 Sep;60(3):794-801. Epub 2012 Aug 14</a>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients: </span>Each softgel contains:</p>\n<p>CoQ10 (as ubiquinol, yeast fermentation source, Kaneka QHTM)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.50 mg</p>\n<p>Grape (Vitis vinifera) seed extract (MegaNatural&reg;-BP,</p>\n<p>standardized to 90% total phenolics, 5% monomers)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;75 mg</p>\n<p>Cocoa (Theobroma cacao) bean extract (ChocamineTM,</p>\n<p>standardized to 12% theombromine)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..125 mg</p>\n<p>Magnesium (Oxide, Citrate)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..150 mg</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients:</span> Sunflower oil, sunflower lecithin, yellow beeswax, ascorbyl palmitate,</p>\n<p>gelatin, glycerin, curcumin, tapioca starch, natural spices/flavours (ginger, allspice, cinnamon).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Free from wheat, gluten, dairy, corn, eggs, nuts, peanuts, fish, shellfish, soy, sugar, GMO,</p>\n<p>artificial colours, flavours and preservatives.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Kaneka QHTM is a trademark&nbsp;of Kaneka Corporation.</p>\n<p>MegaNatural&reg;-BP and&nbsp;its logo are trademarks&nbsp;of Constellation&nbsp;Brands Inc.</p>\n<p>Chocamine&reg; is a registered trademark&nbsp;of New World Enterprises, Inc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The use of ascorbyl palmitate to</p>\n<p>guarantee stability of ubiquinol is</p>\n<p>covered by US Patent 6,740,338.</p>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use:</span> Adults: Take 1 softgel twice daily with meals, or as directed by a qualified</p>\n<p>healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are pregnant, breastfeeding or on</p>\n<p>blood pressure medications or blood thinners. Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out of</p>\n<p>reach of children. Store in a cool dry place to preserve freshness.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">QUALITY, PURITY AND POTENCY GUARANTEED</span>.</p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>', 'Inno-Q-Nol Blood Pressure | CoQ10 | Kaneka QH® Ubiquinol | Chocamine | MegaNatural® BP', 'Inno-Q-Nol  is powered by Kaneka QH® CoQ10 Ubiquinol with patented Q-Nol®  for extended shelf life. Includes patented grape seed and chocolate extracts for blood pressure.   ', 'INNO-Q-NOL™ Tension artérielle', '', '', '', '<p>La tension art&eacute;rielle (ou pression art&eacute;rielle / PA) est la force que le sang exerce sur les parois des art&egrave;res alors qu\\''il circule, et elle permet au sang de couler et de fournir des nutriments au corps. La tension art&eacute;rielle augmente avec l\\''&acirc;ge, et plus de 90% des Canadiens souffriront d\\''hypertension s\\''ils ne modifient pas leur mode de vie. L\\''hypertension est le principal risque de d&eacute;c&egrave;s, et peut causer des accidents vasculaires c&eacute;r&eacute;braux, des crises cardiaques, ainsi que des d&eacute;faillances au niveau du c&oelig;ur et des reins. Elle est &eacute;galement associ&eacute;e &agrave; la d&eacute;mence et aux troubles sexuels. Ces probl&egrave;mes peuvent &ecirc;tre pr&eacute;venus si l\\''hypertension est prise en charge.   La formule Inno-Q-Nol Tension art&eacute;rielle d\\''Inno-Vite utilise comme base le seul ubiquinol stabilis&eacute; (CoQ10 \\"activ&eacute;\\") au Canada et l\\''allie &agrave; un extrait de p&eacute;pins de raisin tr&egrave;s sp&eacute;cial dont l\\''efficacit&eacute; a &eacute;t&eacute; d&eacute;montr&eacute;e en clinique pour abaisser la pression art&eacute;rielle; un extrait de chocolat &eacute;tudi&eacute; en clinique; et du magn&eacute;sium, le tout afin de cr&eacute;er une formule multidimensionnelle naturelle ayant comme but de vous aider &agrave; prendre en charge votre tension art&eacute;rielle.</p>', '', '', '', '', 2, 'No', '', '80043880', 'Active'),
(35, 'vt10216', 1, 'Red Yeast Rice', 'with CoQ10 (ubiquinol) and Vitamin D3', 'Helps promote healthy cholesterol  levels', '<pre>Red yeast rice (RYR) has long been used for cholesterol reduction by practitioners of Traditional&nbsp;&nbsp;</pre>\n<pre>Modern Medicine as it is considered to be a natural source of statins.</pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Helps lower cholesterol naturally</li>\n<li>Contains CoQ10(ubiquinol) and vitamin D<sub>3</sub> </li>\n<li>Includes other natural cholesterol reducing &nbsp;ingredients including Phytosterols, soy-free Lecithin and Choline&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Citrinin-free (Citrinin is kidney damaging toxin linked to some red yeast rice)</li>\n<li>Excellent statin alternative (less side-effects than synthetic statins due to the lower required doses)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>', '<p>Cholesterol is a soft, waxy, fat-like substance found within the bloodstream and cells of the body. It is produced naturally in our bodies and very important for many aspects of human health. Although we need cholesterol to maintain our body&rsquo;s daily functions, too much cholesterol in the blood is a major risk factor for heart disease.</p>\n<p>Red yeast rice (RYR) has long been used for cholesterol reduction by practitioners of Traditional &nbsp;Modern Medicine as it is considered to be a natural source of statins. Statins work by inhibiting the activity of a key enzyme in the biological pathway that creates cholesterol. Although the pharmaceutical option to RYR are statin medications, they utilize the same biological pathway that is also responsible for creating important nutrients such as CoQ10 and vitamin D. Overload of these pathways could affect the supply of critical nutrients needed by our bodies.</p>\n<p><span class=\\" bold\\" style=\\"white-space: pre;\\">Sources:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt;\\"><a href=\\"http://informahealthcare.com/doi/abs/10.3109/14017431003624123\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\">Bogsrud MP, et al. HypoCol (red yeast rice) lowers plasma cholesterol - a randomized placebo controlled study. Scand Cardiovasc J. 2010 Aug;44(4):197-200.</span></a></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22531006\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\">Feuerstein JS, Bjerke WS. Powdered red yeast rice and plant stanols and sterols to lower cholesterol. J Diet Suppl. 2012 Jun;9(2):110-5. Epub 2012 Apr 25.</span></a></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt;\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.ajconline.org/article/S0002-9149(09)02325-X/abstract\\">Halbert SC, et al. Tolerability of red yeast rice (2,400 mg twice daily) versus pravastatin (20 mg twice daily) in patients with previous statin intolerance. Am</a></span></span></span><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.ajconline.org/article/S0002-9149(09)02325-X/abstract\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\">J Cardiol. 2010 Jan 15;105(2):198-204. Epub 2009 Nov 26.</span></a></span></li>\n<li><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt;\\"><a href=\\"http://annals.org/article.aspx?articleid=744541\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\">Becker DJ, et al. Red yeast rice for dyslipidemia in statin-intolerant patients: a randomized trial. Ann Intern Med. 2009 Jun 16;150(12):830-9, W147-9.</span></a></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt;\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\"><a href=\\"http://cpr.sagepub.com/content/14/3/438.abstract\\">Huang CF, et al. Efficacy of Monascus purpureus Went rice on lowering lipid ratios in hypercholesterolemic patients. Eur J Cardiovasc Prev Rehabil. 2007</a>&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><span style=\\"color: #0000ff;\\"><a href=\\"http://cpr.sagepub.com/content/14/3/438.abstract\\">Jun;14(3):438-40.</a></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\"><em><span style=\\"font-size: 7.5pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;\\">For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, optimal health can be achieved. Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health. Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, at every stage of life.</span></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>', '<pre><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients:</span> Each capsule contains:\nRed yeast (Monascus purpureus) rice extract (citrinin-free)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; 300 mg\nCoQ10 (as ubiquinol, yeast fermentation source, Kaneka QHTM)&hellip;........................... 25 mg\nVitamin D3 (cholecalciferol) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;.&hellip;.&hellip;...12.5 mcg (500 IU)\nVitamin C (ascorbic acid) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.............10 mg\nCholine (choline bitartrate) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;...15 mg\nLecithin &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;....15 mg\nPhytosterols (90%) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;.&hellip;.. 200 mg\n<br /></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients:</span> Hydroxypropyl methylcellulose (vegetarian capsule),\nmicrocrystalline cellulose, magnesium stearate.\n\nKaneka QHTM is a trademark of Kaneka Corporation.\n\nFree from wheat, gluten, dairy,\neggs, nuts, peanuts, fish, shellfish,\nsugar, artificial colours, flavours\nor preservatives.</pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"bold\\">QUALITY, PURITY AND POTENCY GUARANTEED.</span></pre>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<pre style=\\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin: 8px;\\"><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use:</span> Adults: Take 1 capsule twice daily with meals, or as directed by a\nqualified healthcare practitioner.</pre>\n<pre style=\\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin: 8px;\\"><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are pregnant, breastfeeding,\non blood pressure medications or blood thinners, or if you have a history of myalgia. May\ncause dizziness, low appetite, nausea, stomach ache or diarrhoea. Do not use if the seal is\nbroken. Keep out of reach of children. Store in a cool dry place to preserve freshness.</pre>', '', '', 'Levure de riz rouge', '', '', '', '<p>Le cholest&eacute;rol est une substance cireuse et lisse ressemblant &agrave; du gras, qu\\''on trouve dans le flot sanguin et dans les cellules du corps. Il est fabriqu&eacute; naturellement par le corps et est tr&egrave;s important dans de nombreux aspects de la sant&eacute; humaine. Bien que nous ayons besoin de cholest&eacute;rol afin de maintenir les fonctions quotidiennes de notre corps, un exc&egrave;s de cholest&eacute;rol dans le sang est un facteur de risque majeur de maladies du c&oelig;ur, et peut mener &eacute;ventuellement &agrave; une crise cardiaque, &agrave; une d&eacute;faillance du corps et m&ecirc;me &agrave; la mort.  La m&eacute;decine moderne traite le cholest&eacute;rol &eacute;lev&eacute; &agrave; l\\''aide de \\"statines\\" qui se classent parmi les m&eacute;dicaments les plus prescrits au monde. Les statines agissent en inhibant l\\''activit&eacute; d\\''une enzyme cl&eacute; dans la voie biologique qui cr&eacute;e le cholest&eacute;rol. Cependant, cette m&ecirc;me voie biologique est &eacute;galement responsable de la production de CoQ10 et de vitamine D qui sont des nutriments essentiels &agrave; notre sant&eacute;.  Les praticiens de la m&eacute;decine traditionnelle utilisent la levure de riz rouge depuis belle lurette dans la r&eacute;duction du cholest&eacute;rol, puisqu\\''elle est la source naturelle employ&eacute;e pour la fabrication des statines. La levure de riz rouge est tout aussi efficace que les statines pharmaceutiques synth&eacute;tiques, mais &agrave; un dosage beaucoup moins &eacute;lev&eacute;. En raison de son dosage plus faible requis et de sa forme naturelle, les effets secondaires courants qu\\''on retrouve avec la prise de statines synth&eacute;tiques se manifestent rarement avec la levure de riz rouge.  La Levure de riz rouge d\\''Inno-Vite est une formule v&eacute;g&eacute;tarienne qui fournit un apport th&eacute;rapeutique quotidien de levure de riz rouge, avec d\\''autres ingr&eacute;dients compl&eacute;mentaires fr&eacute;quemment utilis&eacute;s dans la r&eacute;duction du cholest&eacute;rol. Cependant, cette formule surpasse en bienfaits tout autre produit de levure de riz rouge, car elle livre aussi du CoQ10 ubiquinol et de la vitamine D3 afin de pr&eacute;venir toute carence nutritionnelle.</p>', '', '', '', '', 7, 'No', '', '80037324', 'Active');
