nitions */  table.MsoNormalTable 	{mso-style-name:\\"Table Normal\\"; 	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; 	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; 	mso-style-noshow:yes; 	mso-style-priority:99; 	mso-style-parent:\\"\\"; 	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt; 	mso-para-margin-top:0cm; 	mso-para-margin-right:0cm; 	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt; 	mso-para-margin-left:0cm; 	line-height:115%; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:11.0pt; 	font-family:\\"Calibri\\",\\"sans-serif\\"; 	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; 	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri; 	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-fareast-language:EN-US;} --> <!--[endif] -->\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://ajcn.nutrition.org/content/89/1/71.abstract\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Malaguarnera M, et al. L-Carnitine supplementation reduces oxidized LDL cholesterol in patients with diabetes. Am J Clin Nutr. 2009 Jan;89(1):71-6. Epub 2008 Dec 3.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3403101\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Ghidini O, et al. Evaluation of the therapeutic efficacy of L-carnitine in congestive heart failure. Int J Clin Pharmacol Ther Toxicol. 1988 Apr;26(4):217-20.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://eurjhf.oxfordjournals.org/content/2/2/189.abstract\\" target=\\"_blank\\">G&uuml;rlek A, et al. The effects of L-carnitine treatment on left ventricular function and erythrocyte superoxide dismutase activity in patients with ischemic cardiomyopathy. Eur J Heart Fail. 2000 Jun;2(2):189-93.</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11213533\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Sirtori CR, et al. L-carnitine reduces plasma lipoprotein(a) levels in patients with hyper Lp(a). Nutr Metab Cardiovasc Dis. 2000 Oct;10(5):247-51.</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, optimal health can be achieved. Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health. Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, at every stage of life.</p>', '<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients: </span>Each softgel contains:</div>\n<div>\n<div>CoQ10 (as ubiquinol, yeast fermentation source)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;........ 30 mg</div>\n<div>L-carnitine (fumarate*) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;...250 mg</div>\n<div>Vitamin C (ascorbyl palmitate) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.....12 mg</div>\n<div>Vitamin E (d-alpha tocopheryl acetate) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;...50 mg AT (75 IU)</div>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients</span>: Gelatin, medium chain triglycerides, glycerin,</div>\n<div>\n<div>glycerol triacetate, purified water, high-phosphatidylcholine soy lecithin,</div>\n<div>beeswax, polysorbate 80, titanium dioxide, carob extract.</div>\n&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<div>*L-carnitine fumarate is a stable, highly absorbable form of L-carnitine.</div>\n<div>\n<div>The use of ascorbyl palmitate&nbsp;to guarantee stability of</div>\n<div>ubiquinol is covered by&nbsp;US Patent 6,740,338.</div>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<div>Free from wheat, gluten,</div>\n<div>\n<div>dairy, eggs, nuts, peanuts,</div>\n<div>fish, shellfish, sugar, yeast,</div>\n<div>artificial colours, flavours</div>\n<div>and preservatives.</div>\n<div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">QUALITY, PURITY AND&nbsp;POTENCY GUARANTEED.</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use:</span> Adults: Take 1-3 softgels 1-3 times daily (3-9 softgels</p>\n<p>total), or as directed by a qualified healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are pregnant,</p>\n<p>breastfeeding or on blood pressure medications or blood thinners.</p>\n<p>Sealed for your protection. Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out of</p>\n<p>reach of children. Store in a cool dry place to preserve freshness.</p>', 'Inno-Q-Nol Carnitine | CoQ10 | Ubiquinol | L-Carnitine | metabolism', 'Inno-Q-Nol  is powered by  CoQ10 Ubiquinol with patented Q-Nol®  for extended shelf life. Includes L-Carnitine for metabolism boosting and additional cardiovascular support.   ', 'INNO-Q-NOL<sup>MC</sup> Carnitine', '', '', '', '<p>La carnitine est une substance qui aide le corps &agrave; convertir les gras en &eacute;nergie. La carnitine favorise la sant&eacute; cardiaque.  Carnitine Inno-Q-Nol d\\''Inno-Vite contient du CoQ10 ubiquinol avec stabilit&eacute; garantie gr&acirc;ce &agrave; la licence de brevet exclusive d\\''Inno-Vite, ainsi qu\\''une forme hautement absorbable et stable de L-carnitine. Cette formule pr&eacute;cise a &eacute;t&eacute; &eacute;tudi&eacute;e en clinique avec un groupe de patients, et les r&eacute;sultats ont d&eacute;montr&eacute; des am&eacute;liorations significatives dans la sant&eacute; cardiovasculaire.</p>', '', '', '', '', 3, 'No', '', '80031756', 'Active'),
(37, 'ad-09-09', 3, 'DDS Ultra Cran', '', 'Helps prevent recurrent urinary tract infections', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Utilizes &nbsp;Lactobacillus acidophilus (DDS-1&reg; strain), Bifidobacterium longum (UABL-14), Bifidobacteria bifidum (UABB-10) and Bifidobacterium lactis (UABLA-12)</li>\n<li>Contains 2.5 billion colony forming units (CFU) per serving</li>\n<li>Maintain normal intestinal and vaginal flora throughout every stage of a woman\\''s life</li>\n<li>Formulated with cranberry extract, proven to prevent urinary tract infections (UTIs) due to its ability to stop bacteria from sticking to the surfaces of the urinary wall</li>\n<li>Contributes to a natural healthy gut flora</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">DDS Probiotic Family Overview:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Superior robust strain: Survives stomach acid and bile for a healthy intestinal flora; human origin for easy adaptability.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Clinically researched proprietary formulas: Clinically proven in double blind placebo human trials.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Fortified with prebiotics:&nbsp; Feeds, nourishes and increases probiotic bacteria.</li>\n<li>Complete family care: Full line from infant to urgent care.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Restore the healthy balance of intestinal flora</span></p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Repair the gut ecosystem disrupted by a disturbance (i.e. infection, antibiotic induced diarrhea, etc.)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Reclaim a healthy gut.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">&nbsp;Sources:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.cabdirect.org/abstracts/19800465097.html;jsessionid=46EAA31964AC7726A6DB839218835E16\\" target=\\"_blank\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt;\\">Ayebo, A. D., I. A. Angelo, and K. M. Shahani. 1980. Effect of ingesting&nbsp;</span><em><span style=\\"font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;HelveticaNeueLTStd-LtIt&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-LtIt;\\">Lactobacillus acidophilus&nbsp;</span></em></a><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.cabdirect.org/abstracts/19800465097.html;jsessionid=46EAA31964AC7726A6DB839218835E16\\" target=\\"_blank\\">milk upon fecal flora and enzyme activity in human. Milchwissenschaft, 35: 730-733</a>.</span></li>\n<li><a style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\" href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2064229\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Gerasimov S. V. et al. 2013. Role of probiotics in attenuation of acute respiratory tract infections in preschool</a>&nbsp;<a style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\" href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2064229\\" target=\\"_blank\\">and primary school children. In press.</a></li>\n<li><a style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\" href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20642296\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Gerasimov S. V., Vasjuta V. V., Myhovych O. O., Bondarchuk L. I. 2010. Probiotic supplement reduces atopic dermatits in preschool children. Am J Clin Dermatol, 11:351-361</a><span style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\">.</span></li>\n<li><a style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\" href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14968899\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Gerasimov S. V. 2004. Probiotic prophylaxis in pediatric recurrent urinary tract infections. Clin Pediatr., 43:95-98.</a></li>\n<li><a style=\\"font-family: HelveticaNeueLTStd-Lt, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\\" href=\\"http://www.probioticsincanada.com/en/pdfs/IBS%20Study-%20Published%20Article.pdf\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Nagala R., Routray C. 2011. Clinical Case Study&mdash;Multispecies probiotic supplement minimizes symptoms of irritable bowel syndrome. US Gastroenterol Hepatol., 7: 36-37.</a></li>\n</ul>', '<p>Medicinal Ingredients: Each capsule contains:</p>\n<p>D-Mannose. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 200 mg</p>\n<p>Cranberry (Vaccinium macrocarpon) fruit juice extract (8-10:1). . . . . . . . . . . . . 50 mg</p>\n<p>Lactobacillus acidophilus (DDS&reg;-1 strain). . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 1.25 billion cfu</p>\n<p>Bifidobacterium longum (UABL-14). . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 0.42 billion cfu</p>\n<p>Bifidobacterium lactis (UABLA-12). . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 0.42 billion cfu</p>\n<p>Bifidobacterium bifidum (UABB-10). . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 0.41 billion cfu</p>\n<p>Non Medicinal Ingredients: Vegetable cellulose, FOS, rice maltodextrin, magnesium</p>\n<p>stearate, magnesium hydroxide and tricalcium phosphate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNoSpacing\\">DDS&reg; is a registered trademark of UAS Laboratories, Inc.</p>', '<p>Directions for Use: Adults: Take 2 capsules daily on an empty stomach, or as directed by</p>\n<p>a healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<p>Cautions: Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are pregnant, breastfeeding,</p>\n<p>taking blood thinners, or have a history of kidney stones. Consult a health care practitioner</p>\n<p>if UTI symptoms persist or worsen. Discontinue use and consult a health care practitioner if</p>\n<p>symptoms of digestive upset (e.g. diarrhoea) occur, worsen, or persist beyond 3 days.</p>\n<p>Sealed for your protection. Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out of reach of children.</p>\n<p>Keep refrigerated once opened. Do not freeze.</p>\n<p>Contraindications: Do not use if you are experiencing nausea, fever, vomiting, bloody</p>\n<p>diarrhoea or severe abdominal pain; or if you have an immune-compromised condition (e.g.</p>\n<p>AIDS, lymphoma, patients undergoing long-term corticosteroid treatment)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>QUALITY, PURITY AND POTENCY GUARANTEED.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Free from dairy, corn, wheat, gluten, soy, nuts, peanuts, eggs, fish, shellfish, yeast, GMO,</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNoSpacing\\">or artificial colours, flavours, or preservatives.</p>', '', '', 'DDS ULTA CRAN', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 7, 'No', '', '80034766', 'Active'),
(38, 'sb10205', 4, 'Vitamin K2 Drops Extra Strength', '', 'Promotes healthy bones', '<p>Formulation includes Vitamin K2 from &nbsp;MK-7, the only Canadian vitamin K2 free from the syntetic anti-foaming chemical, dimethyl polysiloxane. &nbsp;Higher levels of Vitamin K are strongly associated with better bone mass, heavier bone density, improved bone geometry and overall mineral content because it activates a special protein called osteocalcin that works synergistically with &nbsp;calcium to build healthy bone tissue. Strong bones developed in childhood and maintained in adulthood reduce the risk of osteoporotic fractures. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\\"bold\\">Safest and most effective form of Vitamin K2:&nbsp;</span>Formulated with MK-7, which helps improve activation of osteocalcin.</li>\n<li><span class=\\"bold\\">Improves blood stability:&nbsp;</span>Vitamin K2 provides longer blood half-life.</li>\n</ul>', '<p>Specific forms of K2, like MK-7, have a very long half life in</p>\n<p>circulation, giving the body a steady supply of vitamin K2 24 hours a day.</p>\n<p>Innovite Health\\''s Vitamin K2 contains natural Vitamin K2 in its most</p>\n<p>absorbable form to promote optimum bone health and it is the only MK-7</p>\n<p>product in Canada free from the synthetic anti-foaming chemical, dimethyl</p>\n<p>polysiloxane.</p>\n<p>Vitamin K2 is vital in supporting bone health &nbsp;Inno-Vite\\''s Vitamin K2 Drops contains contains the safest and the most effective form of Vitamin K2 as MK-7 and has been shown to be the optimal vitamin K2 product with longer blood half-life (resulting in more stable blood levels) and better effect on bone and cardiovascular health through the activation of osteocalcin and MGP</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Better effect on bone and cardiovascular health through the activation of osteocalcin and MGP</li>\n<li>MGP&nbsp; is the most potent inhibitor of soft tissue calcification currently known. When activated by vitamin K, MGP prevents calcium from building up in the arteries</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vitamin K is required in order to use calcium in the process of creating a</p>\n<p>healthy bone matrix. It activates a protein called &ldquo;osteocalcin&rdquo;, which is</p>\n<p>involved in the bone-building process. Osteocalcin binds calcium to the</p>\n<p>bone, thus strengthening the skeleton. Insufficient vitamin K leads to inactive</p>\n<p>osteocalcin that cannot bind calcium to the surface of the bone.</p>\n<p>Higher levels of Vitamin K are strongly associated with better bone mass,</p>\n<p>better bone density, improved bone geometry and improved mineral</p>\n<p>content. Strong bones developed in childhood and maintained in adulthood</p>\n<p>reduce the risk of osteoporotic fractures.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the same time, vitamin K activates another protein called MGP &ndash; the most</p>\n<p>potent inhibitor of soft tissue calcification currently known. When activated</p>\n<p>by vitamin K, MGP prevents calcium from building up in the arteries.</p>\n<p>Two naturally-occurring forms of vitamin K have been identified, and these</p>\n<p>are designated as vitamin K1 and K2. Natural Vitamin K2 is the source of</p>\n<p>vitamin K preferred by all tissues including cartilage, bone and soft tissues.</p>', '<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Medicinal Ingredients: Each drop (0.05 mL) contains:</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Vitamin K2 (MK-7 from Bacillus subtilis natto)................30 mcg</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNor