(41, 'vt10233', 1, 'INNO-KRILL + Astaxanthin', '', '', '', '<p>Natural Cardiovascular and Cognitive Support  Astaxanthin is a naturally-occurring carotenoid. Due to its unique structure, it provides a wide range of antioxidant benefits. Astaxanthin can help protect cell membranes against free-radical attack and pot</p>', '', '', '', '', 'INNO-KRILL + Astaxanthine', '', '', '', '<p>INNO-KRILL + Astaxanthine -Soutien cardiovasculaire et cognitif.  L\\''astaxanthine est un carot&eacute;no&iuml;de qui est produit naturellement. En raison de sa structure unique, elle pr&eacute;sente une panoplie de bienfaits antioxydants. L\\''astaxanthine peut aider &agrave; prot&eacute;ger les membranes cellulaires contre l\\''attaque des radicaux libres, et potentialise l\\''action des autres antioxydants tels que les vitamines E et C. Des &eacute;tudes scientifiques ont r&eacute;v&eacute;l&eacute; que l\\''astaxanthine peut aider &agrave; soutenir une r&eacute;ponse inflammatoire saine, &agrave; renforcer les fonctions immunitaires et &agrave; procurer un soutien neurologique. Selon des &eacute;tudes r&eacute;centes, l\\''astaxanthine pourrait m&ecirc;me contribuer &agrave; soutenir la structure de la peau durant une exposition &agrave; la lumi&egrave;re solaire.  Inno-Vite Inno-Krill + Astaxanthine est une source riche en phospholipides sous forme d\\''AEP et d\\''ADH d&eacute;riv&eacute;s de l\\''huile de krill, avec adjonction d\\''astaxanthine dans le but de soutenir la sant&eacute; cardiovasculaire et la sant&eacute; cognitive. Chaque g&eacute;lule contient 600 mg d\\''huile de krill EKO<sup>MC</sup> et 4 mg d\\''astaxanthine.</p>', '', '', '', '', 11, 'No', '', '', 'Disable'),
(42, 'vt10223', 1, 'Magnesium Glycinate', '', 'Helps in the maintenance of proper muscle function and tissue formation, while assisting to metabolize carbohydrates, fats and proteins.', '<p>Magnesium is very important for the normal functioning of cells, nerves, muscles, bones, and the heart. &nbsp;Our Magnesium Glycinate formula also includes potassium&nbsp;- a simple mineral with a &nbsp;helps trigger your heart\\''s squeeze of blood through your body.</p>\n<p>Key Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Potential to be more gentle on the bowel.</li>\n<li>Highly absorbable (5x more than magnesium oxide)</li>\n<li>Powder format great for patients with sensitivities to oral formats.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>INNO-VITE Magnesium Glycinate helps in the maintenance of proper muscle function and tissue formation; in the development and maintenance of bones and teeth; also assists the body to metabolize carbohydrates, fats and proteins.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Magnesium Glycinate tends to be less disruptive to the bowel, keeping stool loose and avoiding potential for constipation. It is also highly absorbable, almost 5x that of magnesium oxide.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<em><span style=\\"font-size: 7.5pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;\\">For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, optimal health can be achieved. Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health. Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, at every stage of life.</span></em></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\"><span><em>&nbsp;</em></span></p>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients: </span>Each rounded scoop (6 g) contains:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Magnesium (glycinate) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.500 mg</p>\n<p>Potassium (chloride) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;99 mg</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients:</span> Natural orange flavour, colloidal silicon</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>dioxide, stevia, xylitol, sorbitol, dextrates.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out of reach of children. Store in a</p>\n<p>cool, dry place to preserve</p>\n<p>freshness.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>QUALITY, PURITY AND</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>POTENCY GUARANTEED.</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Free from wheat, gluten,</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>nuts, peanuts, soy, eggs,</p>\n<p>dairy, fish, shellfish, yeast,</p>\n<p>artificial flavours, colours and</p>\n<p>preservatives.</p>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use:</span> Adults (19 years and over): Take half a scoop</p>\n<p>mixed in water once or twice daily with a meal, or as directed by</p>\n<p>a healthcare practitioner. Drink immediately after mixing.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Some people may experience diarrhoea with doses greater</p>\n<p>than 350 mg/day.</p>', '', '', 'Magnesium Glycinate', '', '', '', '<p>INNO-VITE Glycinate de magn&eacute;sium aide au bon maintien des fonctions musculaires et &agrave; la formation des tissus; au d&eacute;veloppement et au maintien des os et des dents; et aide aussi le corps &agrave; m&eacute;taboliser les glucides, les lipides et les prot&eacute;ines. L\\''adjonction de potassium dans cette formule aide &agrave; maximiser la r&eacute;tention du magn&eacute;sium par le corps.</p>', '', '', '', '', 11, 'No', '', '80038935', 'Active'),
(43, 'ace-60', 6, 'Acetyl-L-Carnitine', '', 'Helps slow the progression of Alzheimer’s disease and improve overall cognitive function including memory, attention and reaction time.', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Helps the body metabolize fats</li>\n<li>Boosts energy metabolism for optimum cardiovascular health</li>\n<li>Excellent option for people that experience difficulties swallowing tablets &nbsp;</li>\n</ul>', '<p>L-carnitine is an amino acid (a building block for proteins) that is naturally produced in the body and &nbsp;helps the body turn fat into energy. The body produces it in the liver and kidneys and stores it in the skeletal muscles, heart, brain and sperm. Some people, however, may not have enough carnitine because their bodies cannot make enough or can&rsquo;t transport it into tissues so it can be used. It has been proposed as a treatment for many conditions because it acts as an antioxidant. Antioxidants fight harmful particles in the body known as free radicals, which damage cells and tamper with DNA. Antioxidants can neutralize free radicals and may reduce or help prevent some of the damage they cause. Sometime this is also taken &nbsp;to increase L-carnitine levels in people whose natural level of L-carnitine is too low because they have a genetic disorder, are taking certain drugs (<a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/drug-8885-valproic+acid+oral.aspx\\">valproic acid</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/epilepsy/understanding-seizures-basics\\">seizures</a>), or because they are undergoing a medical procedure (hemodialysis for&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/urinary-incontinence-oab/picture-of-the-kidneys\\">kidney</a>&nbsp;disease) that uses up the body&rsquo;s L-carnitine&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sources:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/supplement/carnitine-lcarnitine#ixzz2ohJJAA9a\\">Carnitine (L-carnitine) University of Maryland Medical Center</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\"></a><a href=\\"http://archneur.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=592016\\">Sano M, et al. Double-blind parallel design pilot study of acetyl levocarnitine in patients with Alzheimer\\''s disease. Arch Neurol. 1992 Nov;49(11):1137-41.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.aggjournal.com/article/S0167-4943(07)00106-9/abstract\\">Malaguarnera M, et al. Acetyl L-carnitine (ALC) treatment in elderly patients with fatigue. Arch Gerontol Geriatr. 2008 Mar-Apr;46(2):181-90. Epub 2007 Jul 20.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10750638?dopt=Abstract\\">Turpeinen AK, et al. Long-term effect of acetyl-L-carnitine on myocardial 123I-MIBG uptake in patients with diabetes. Clin Auton Res. 2000 Feb;10(1):13-6.</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, optimal health can be achieved. Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health. Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, at every stage of life.</p>', '<p><span style=\\"color: #231f20; font-family: ArialNarrow-Bold; font-size: xx-small;\\"><span style=\\"color: #231f20; font-family: ArialNarrow-Bold; font-size: xx-small;\\"><span style=\\"color: #231f20; font-family: ArialNarrow-Bold; font-size: xx-small;\\"><strong>Medicinal Ingredients: </strong></span></span></span><span style=\\"colo