(46, 'vt10236', 1, 'Pterostilbene', 'Resveratrol-type blueberry phytonutrient', 'An antioxidant for the maintenance of good health.', '<div>\n<pre>Pterostilbene (pronounced &ldquo;tero-STILL-bean&rdquo;)&nbsp; is a compound naturally found in blueberries, and may help </pre>\n<pre>maintain healthy cholesterol, blood pressure and blood glucose levels.</pre>\n<h5><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></h5>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Significantly better absorption, metabolic stability and biological activity than resveratrol </li>\n<li>Provides high amounts of this valuable phytonutrient, without consuming unrealistic amounts of blueberries.</li>\n<li>Contains a blueberry extract with its natural mix of phytonutrients to enhance the benefits of pterostilbene</li>\n</ul>\n<pre> </pre>', '<pre>Blueberries, like most berries, contain a number of unique therapeutic compounds beneficial to human health. </pre>\n<pre>In particular, blueberries contain pterostilbene (pronounced tero-STILL-been), a natural and powerful antioxidant. </pre>\n<pre> </pre>\n<h5><span class=\\"bold\\">Therapeutic benefits include:</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li>Cardiovascular: Supports healthy blood flow and circulation; helps maintain healthy blood pressure alreadywithin the normal ranges; promotes nitric oxide synthesis.</li>\n<li>Cognitive: May improve memory and mental focus; may enhance mood and feeling of well-being.</li>\n<li>Blood sugar: May help support healthy blood sugar levels by raising the body&rsquo;s production of insulin</li>\n<li>Anti-aging: May help fight free-radicals caused by oxidative stress</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h5>Sources:</h5>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\\"https://www.thieme-connect.com/DOI/DOI?10.1055/s-2005-864130\\">Hougee S, et al. Selective COX-2 inhibition by a Pterocarpus marsupium extract characterized by</a> <a href=\\"https://www.thieme-connect.com/DOI/DOI?10.1055/s-2005-864130\\">pterostilbene, and its activity in healthy human volunteers. Planta Med. 2005 May;71(5):387-92.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://carcin.oxfordjournals.org/content/31/7/1272.long\\">Paul S, et al. Dietary intake of pterostilbene, a constituent of blueberries, inhibits the beta-catenin/p65 downstream signaling pathway and colon carcinogenesis in rats. Carcinogenesis. 2010 Jul;31(7):1272-8. Epub 2010 Jan 8</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.altmedrev.com/publications/15/2/159.pdf\\">[No authors listed]. Pterostilbene. Monograph. Altern Med Rev. 2010 Jul;15(2):159-63.</a></li>\n</ul>\n<pre><br /></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"italic\\">For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, </span></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"italic\\">optimal health can be achieved.  Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients</span></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"italic\\">and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health.  Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest </span></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"italic\\">research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, </span></pre>\n<pre><span class=\\"italic\\">at every stage of life.</span></pre>', '<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><strong style=\\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-family: BentonSansComp-Medium;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Medicinal Ingredients: </span></span></strong></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-family: BentonSansComp-Medium;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Each vegetarian capsule contains:</span></span></p>\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-family: BentonSansComp-Medium;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">Pterostilbene &hellip