(47, 'br10209', 6, 'INNO-Q-NOL<sup>®</sup> Ultrasorb<sup>®</sup> ', 'Kaneka QH® CoQ10 Ubiquinol', 'Helps improve the functioning of the central nervous system and reduce the frequency of migraine headaches.', '<p>Coenzyme Q10 is a vital nutrient present in mitochondria of every cell in the body. It plays a critical role in energy production within the cells of the nervous system, including the brain.</p>\n<p>By restoring and repairing the healthy cells in your body and protecting them from free cell radicals, you will be able to reclaim your cognitive health to achieve a stronger and longer lasting wellness.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Helps support the functioning of the central nervous system</li>\n<li>Reduces the Frequency of Migraine headaches</li>\n<li>Provides additional cognitive support if use is combined with PQQ</li>\n<li>Formulated with Ubiquinol, the biologically superior form of CoQ10:</li>\n<li>Strongest lipid soluble antioxidant available</li>\n<li>Most circulating CoQ10 (95%) in the blood</li>\n<li>Highly stabilized through a patented process from Kaneka Corporation, Japan &ndash; the world\\''s largest CoQ10 producer and the makers of the only yeast fermented, most stable form of CoQ10.</li>\n<li><span style=\\"text-indent: -18pt;\\">Especially beneficial for those who cannot efficiently convert less active forms of CoQ10 into ubiquinol</span></li>\n</ul>', '<p><span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">About CoQ10</span></p>\n<p>Coenzyme Q10 (CoQ10) is an extremely important nutrient that every cell in your body must have in order to produce energy. It is naturally found in the energy-producing center of the cell known as the mitochondria, the part of a cell responsible for the production of energy in the form of ATP (Adenosine triphosphate). ATP serves as the cell\\''s major energy source and drives a number of biological processes, including muscle contraction and the production of protein. CoQ10 is involved in making this important molecule.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Ubiquinone vs. Ubiquinol</span></p>\n<p>Ubiquinone is the standard form of CoQ10. The body must automatically convert ubiquinone to ubiquinol - the most body-ready form of CoQ10 - to help in cell energy production by providing quick and efficient replenishment.&nbsp; Aging inhibits this conversion process hence the requirement for CoQ10 supplementation, where the body-ready ubiquinol form may achieve the most optimal benefits. Human clinical studies have shown that when compared to standard CoQ10 supplements ubiquinol is: 8x better absorbed in the bloodstream; reduces exercise-induced fatigue by 90%; and slows aging by 40%.</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Kaneka QH&reg; Ubiquinol&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Ubiquinol by nature is not stable (i.e. reverts back to ubiquinone). Kaneka Corporation, the world\\''s primary CoQ10 producer, has developed a patented process that creates the most highly stabilized form of ubiquinol as a raw ingredient - Kaneka QH&reg; Ubiquinol.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"italic\\">For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy,  optimal health can be achieved.  Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health.  Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest  research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs,  at every stage of life.</span>&nbsp;</p>', '<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients:</span> Each softgel contains:</div>\n<div>Coenzyme Q10 (<span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">Kaneka QH&reg;</span>&nbsp;ubiquinol, from yeast fermentation) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;100 mg</div>\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients: </span>Medium chain triglycerides, glycerin, gelatin, ascorbyl</div>\n<div>\n<div>palmitate, purified water, polysorbate 80, annatto extract, soybean oil.</div>\n&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<div>QUALITY, PURITY AND POTENCY GUARANTEED.</div>\n</div>\n<div>Free from wheat, gluten, dairy,</div>\n<div>\n<div>corn, eggs, nuts, peanuts, fish,</div>\n<div>shellfish, yeast, sugar, artificial</div>\n<div>colours, flavours and</div>\n<div>preservatives.</div>\n</div>\n<div><span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">Kaneka QH&reg;</span>&nbsp;is a trademark of Kaneka Corporation.</div>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for use:</span> Adults: Take 1 softgel 1-3 times daily.</p>\n<p>For migraine prevention (adults): Take 1 softgel 2-3 times daily.</p>\n<p>Use for a minimum of 3 months to see beneficial effects.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Warnings:</span> Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are pregnant,</p>\n<p>breastfeeding or on blood pressure medications or blood thinners.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out of reach of children. Store in a</p>\n<p>cool dry place to preserve freshness.</p>', '', '', 'INNO-Q-NOL<sup>®</sup> Ultrasorb<sup>®</sup>', '', '', '', '<p>INNO-Q-NOL<sup>&reg;</sup> Ultrasorb<sup>&reg;</sup> est la forme la plus bioactive et la plus biodisponible de CoQ10 offert sur le march&eacute; pour am&eacute;liorer le fonctionnement du syst&egrave;me nerveux central et pour r&eacute;duire la fr&eacute;quence des migraines.</p>', '', '', '', '', 5, 'No', '', '80023355', 'Active'),
(48, 'br10110', 6, 'Melatonin', '', 'Provides sleep support by helping regulate circadian rhythm, and improve sleep quality related to sleep disorders and/or jetlag.', '<p>Melatonin is a natural sleep hormone produced at night by the brain and helps regulate other hormones and maintains the body\\''s circadian rhythm. Restore the melatonin levels in your body by using &nbsp; Melatonin to repair your body&rsquo;s normal circadian rhythm. Reclaim your sleep and energy and have a great day!</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>6-8 hour sustained-release Melatonin to ensure a lasting effect during sleep time</li>\n<li>Provides sleep support by helping to regulate the body&rsquo;s circadian rhythm</li>\n<li><span style=\\"text-indent: -18pt;\\">Improves sleep quality related to sleep disorders and/or jetlag.&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<div>Melatonin is a hormone produced by the pineal gland, the organ that helps re-set the body&rsquo;s sleep-wake cycle (aspect of the circadian rhythm). It promotes the sleep cycle by helping to increase the total sleep time (aspect of sleep quality) in people suffering from sleep restriction or altered sleep schedule (e.g. shift-work and jet lag). It also helps to reduce the time it takes to fall asleep in people with delayed sleep phase syndrome</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', '<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients:</span> Each vegetarian capsule contains:</div>\n<div>\n<div>Melatonin (N-acetyl-5-methoxytryptamine)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;3 mg</div>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients:</span> Hydroxypropyl methylcellulose (vegetarian capsule),</div>\n<div>\n<div>microcystalline cellulose, magnesium stearate, silicon dioxide.</div>\n</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">QUALITY, PURITY AND POTENCY GUARANTEED.</span></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Free from wheat, gluten, soy,</div>\n<div>\n<div>corn, dairy, yeast, sugar, eggs,</div>\n<div>nuts, peanuts, fish, shellfish,</div>\n<div>GMO, artificial colours,</div>\n<div>flavours and preservatives.</div>\n</div>', '<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use:</span> Adults: Take 2 capsules, once per day before bedtime, or as</p>\n<p>directed by a healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Warnings: </span>For use beyond 4 weeks, consult a healthcare practitioner. Use at or before</p>\n<p>bedtime. Do not use if pregnant or breastfeeding. Consult a healthcare practitioner</p>\n<p>prior to use if you have a hormonal disorder, diabetes, liver or kidney disease, cerebral</p>\n<p>palsy, seizure disorders, migraine, depression and/or hypertension, or if you are taking</p>\n<p>blood pressure or sedative/hypnotic medications. If symptoms persist continuously for</p>\n<p>more than 4 weeks (chronic insomnia), consult your healthcare practitioner.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Contraindications:</span> Do not use if you are taking immunosuppressive drugs. Do not</p>\n<p>drive or use machinery for 5 hours after taking melatonin.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Do not use if seal is broken. Keep out of reach of children. Keep bottle</p>\n<p>tightly closed. Store between 15 - 30&deg;C.</p>', '', '', 'Mélatonine', '', '', '', '<p>Soutien pour le sommeil  La m&eacute;latonine est une hormone du sommeil naturelle s&eacute;cr&eacute;t&eacute;e par le cerveau pendant la nuit et elle aide &agrave; moduler les autres hormones et g&egrave;re les rythmes circadiens du corps. Le produit M&eacute;latonine avec 6 &agrave; 8 heures de lib&eacute;ration soutenue d\\''Innovite Health procure un soutien en aidant &agrave; r&eacute;guler le rythme circadien du corps et &agrave; am&eacute;liorer la qualit&eacute; du sommeil relativement aux troubles du sommeil et/ou au d&eacute;calage horaire.</p>', '', '', '', '', 7, 'No', '', '80007358', 'Active'),
(49, 'vt10237', 1, 'Acetyl-L-Carnitine', '', 'Helps to maintain proper muscle function', '<pre><span class=\\"bold\\">Key Benefits: </span></pre>\n<pre>&bull; Helps the body metabolize fats </pre>\n<pre>&bull; Boosts energy metabolism for optimum cardiovascular health</pre>\n<pre>&bull; Excellent option for people that experience difficulties swallowing tablets</pre>', '<p>L-carnitine is an amino acid (a building block for proteins) that is naturally produced in the body and &nbsp;helps the body turn fat into energy. The body produces it in the liver and kidneys and stores it in the skeletal muscles, heart, brain and sperm. Some people, however, may not have enough carnitine because their bodies cannot make enough or can&rsquo;t transport it into tissues so it can be used. It has been proposed as a treatment for many conditions because it acts as an antioxidant. Antioxidants fight harmful particles in the body known as free radicals, which damage cells and tamper with DNA. Antioxidants can neutralize free radicals and may reduce or help prevent some of the damage they cause. Sometime this is also taken &nbsp;to increase L-carnitine levels in people whose natural level of L-carnitine is too low because they have a genetic disorder, are taking certain drugs (<a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/drug-8885-valproic+acid+oral.aspx\\">valproic acid</a> for <a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/epilepsy/understanding-seizures-basics\\">seizures</a>), or because they are undergoing a medical procedure (hemodialysis for <a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/urinary-incontinence-oab/picture-of-the-kidneys\\">kidney</a> disease) that uses up the body&rsquo;s L-carnitine&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sources:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/supplement/carnitine-lcarnitine#ixzz2ohJJAA9a\\">Carnitine (L-carnitine) University of Maryland Medical Center</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\"></a><a href=\\"http://archneur.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=592016\\">Sano M, et al. Double-blind parallel design pilot study of acetyl levocarnitine in patients with Alzheimer\\''s disease. Arch Neurol. 1992 Nov;49(11):1137-41.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.aggjournal.com/article/S0167-4943(07)00106-9/abstract\\">Malaguarnera M, et al. Acetyl L-carnitine (ALC) treatment in elderly patients with fatigue. Arch Gerontol Geriatr. 2008 Mar-Apr;46(2):181-90. Epub 2007 Jul 20.</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10750638?dopt=Abstract\\">Turpeinen AK, et al. Long-term effect of acetyl-L-carnitine on myocardial 123I-MIBG uptake in patients with diabetes. Clin Auton Res. 2000 Feb;10(1):13-6.</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\\"italic\\">For over 30 years, Innovite Health has been inspiring wellness. When the body&rsquo;s core systems work in synergy, optimal health can be achieved. Our goal to nourish and heal the body from the inside out: restoring nutrients and repairing damage so you can reclaim your health. Our nutritional foundation is built from the latest research and clinical evidence. Safe, natural and effective &ndash; Innovite Health for your body&rsquo;s needs, at every stage of life.</span></p>', '<div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Medicinal Ingredients:</span></div>\n<div>Each tablespoon (15 mL) contains:</div>\n<div>L-carnitine</div>\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From acetyl-L-carnitine&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;750 mg</div>\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From L-carnitine&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;750 mg</div>\n<div>Magnesium (gluconate)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;20 mg</div>\n</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Non-medicinal Ingredients:</span> purified water, sodium citrate, natural</div>\n<div>\n<div>fruit punch flavour, purified stevia extract.</div>\n</div>', '<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Directions for Use</span>: Adults: Take 1 tablespoon (15 mL) once daily,</div>\n<div>\n<div>preferably away from meals, or as directed by a healthcare practitioner.</div>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\\"bold\\">Cautions:</span> Consult a healthcare practitioner prior to use if you are</div>\n<div>\n<div>pregnant or breastfeeding. Do not use if the seal is broken. Keep out</div>\n<div>of reach of children. Refrigerate after opening to preserve freshness.</div>\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '<p>Non-medicinal Ingredients: purified water, sodium citrate, natural fruit punch flavour, purified stevia extract.</p>', '<p>L-carnitine is an amino acid (a building block for proteins) that is naturally produced in the body and &nbsp;helps the body turn fat into energy. The body produces it in the liver and kidneys and stores it in the skeletal muscles, heart, brain and sperm. Some people, however, may not have enough carnitine because their bodies cannot make enough or can&rsquo;t transport it into tissues so it can be used. It has been proposed as a treatment for many conditions because it acts as an antioxidant. Antioxidants fight harmful particles in the body known as free radicals, which damage cells and tamper with DNA. Antioxidants can neutralize free radicals and may reduce or help prevent some of the damage they cause. Sometime this is also taken &nbsp;to increase L-carnitine levels in people whose natural level of L-carnitine is too low because they have a genetic disorder, are taking certain <a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/index-drugs.aspx\\">drugs</a> (<a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/drugs/drug-8885-valproic+acid+oral.aspx\\">valproic acid</a> for <a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/epilepsy/understanding-seizures-basics\\">seizures</a>), or because they are undergoing a medical procedure (hemodialysis for <a href=\\"http://www.webmd.com/urinary-incontinence-oab/picture-of-the-kidneys\\">kidney</a> disease) that uses up the body&rsquo;s L-carnitine&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sources:</p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://umm.edu/health/medical/altmed/supplement/carnitine-lcarnitine#ixzz2ohJJAA9a\\">Carnitine (L-carnitine) University of Maryland Medical Center</a></p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a></p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\">Spagnoli A, et al. Long-term acetyl-L-carnitine treatment in Alzheimer\\''s disease. Neurology. 1991 Nov;41(11):1726-32.</a></p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1944900\\"></a><a href=\\"http://archneur.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=592016\\">Sano M, et al. Double-blind parallel design pilot study of acetyl levocarnitine in patients with Alzheimer\\''s disease. Arch Neurol. 1992 Nov;49(11):1137-41.</a></p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://archneur.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=592016\\"></a><a name=\\"_Hlk377187280\\"></a><a href=\\"http://www.aggjournal.com/article/S0167-4943(07)00106-9/abstract\\">Malaguarnera M, et al. Acetyl L-carnitine (ALC) treatment in elderly patients with fatigue. Arch Gerontol Geriatr. 2008 Mar-Apr;46(2):181-90. Epub 2007 Jul 20.</a></p>\n<p>&bull; <a href=\\"http://www.aggjournal.com/article/S0167-4943(07)00106-9/abstract\\"></a><a href=\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10750638?dopt=Abstract\\">Turpeinen AK, et al. Long-term effect of acetyl-L-carnitine on myocardial 123I-MIBG uptake in patients with diabetes. Clin Auton Res. 2000 Feb;10(1):13-6.</a></p>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>', '<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\\"> </span></p>', '', '', '', 9, 'Yes', '', '80042763', 'Active');
