(46, 1, '2011-01-27 23:37:54', '2011-01-27 23:37:54', 'Ubiquinol is the active antioxidant form of Coenzyme Q10 (CoQ10) that your body can readily use. A note to those taking regular CoQ10 (ubiquinone), our bodies must first convert CoQ10 into ubiquinol prior to it being used, and this conversion decreases with age and various health conditions. Produced naturally within the body, ubiquinol is CoQ10 that has been converted into a substance necessary for use in cellular energy production. In addition to its critical role in energy production, it is one of the most powerful fat-soluble antioxidants available, protecting the body’s cells from damage caused by oxidative stress and free radicals.\r\n\r\nSome benefits of taking this miracle supplement are:\r\n<h2>Anti-fatigue:</h2>\r\n<strong></strong>A study to compare the anti-fatigue effects of the ubiquinol and ubiquinone forms of CoQ10 showed that aged rats receiving regular CoQ10 had a 60% increase in running time while the group receiving ubiquinol had a 150% increase in running time.\r\n<h2>Congestive Heart Failure (CHF):</h2>\r\n<strong></strong>This is the condition where dramatic improvements have been seen the most. The cardiologists leading the study called ubiquinol a “major breakthrough” after seeing CHF patients return to health from their death beds.\r\n<h2>Diabetes:</h2>\r\n<strong></strong>Type 2 diabetics suffer from elevated oxidative stress, which rapidly depletes ubiquinol levels. In fact, in studies, diabetics had approximately 75% less ubiquinol than the nondiabetic control group. Another study showed that supplementing with regular CoQ10 had no effect on blood levels of ubiquinol in relation to CoQ10, which indicates the importance of taking the active  ubiquinol form directly.\r\n<h2>Migraine prevention:</h2>\r\n<strong></strong>Health Canada has approved the use of ubiquinol in migraine prevention.A decrease in frequency and severity can be expected after a minimum of three months of daily supplementation.\r\n<h2>Statin drugs for cholesterol:</h2>\r\n<strong></strong>Ubiquinol is essential for anyone taking a statin drug. Statin drugs work to lower your cholesterol by inhibiting the same pathway your body uses to produce CoQ10. CoQ10 deficiency resulting from these drugs is what’s considered to be one of the main factors in why statins are notorious for its frequent and serious side effects. Up to 300 mg/day of ubiquinol may be needed to restore CoQ10 levels.\r\n\r\nSo, while ubiquinol is typically seen as a “heart health” product, its use is now spreading and becoming more of an overall anti-aging supplement – that’s backed-up by considerable scientific evidence. Whether for prevention or treatment of age-related illness, be sure to consider ubiquinol.', 'A wonder supplement - CoQ10 UBIQUINOL', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'a-wonder-supplement-coq10-ubiquinol', '', '', '2011-01-27 23:50:35', '2011-01-27 23:50:35', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=46', 0, 'post', '', 0),
