(73, 1, '2011-02-25 13:01:46', '2011-02-25 13:01:46', 'Black walnuts are a rich source of nutritionally important ingredients. They have significant amounts of magnesium and potassium. They contain essential Omega-3 and Omega 6 fatty acids that are particularly beneficial to the heart. Having a handful of walnuts everyday can promote heart health and reduce the chances of heart attack and stroke. Studies have shown that eating walnuts can lower high cholesterol levels.\r\n\r\nIntake of black walnuts positively affects the arteries as they decrease the inflammation and reduce the level of substances that block the arteries. They aid in enhancing the circulation of blood throughout the body. Since black walnuts have omega-3 fatty acids, they also help to treat several conditions like asthma, high blood pressure and even cancer. People suffering from heartburn have also found relief by including black walnuts in their diet. A study revealed that black walnuts can kill candida, which is a yeast-like fungus. They are even better than most anti-fungal drugs.\r\n\r\nExternal application of black walnuts is also useful in the treatment of skin conditions like psoriasis and canker sores. They can successfully heal skin problems that occur due to fungal infections. Some doctors also recommend taking walnut extracts internally for disorders like rheumatism, gout, glandular disturbances, and those that occur due to parasites. When taken internally, the extract oxygenates the blood thereby destroying the parasites.', 'Black Walnut —  Miracle in a nutshell!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'black-walnut-miracle-in-a-nutshell', '', '', '2011-02-25 16:11:19', '2011-02-25 16:11:19', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=73', 0, 'post', '', 0),
