(109, 1, '2011-02-25 13:26:45', '2011-02-25 13:26:45', 'Olive leaf extract is derived from the leaves of the olive tree, which is a small evergreen tree native to the Mediterranean region. The recorded benefits of olive leaf extract spans eons going all the way back to the ancient Mediterranean culture.\r\n\r\nThe Greek physician Hippocrates, also known as the "father of medicine," prescribed olive oil to treat muscular pains, ulcers and cholera. Numerous folk medicine uses for olive and olive leaf have sprung up in various cultures.\r\n\r\n<strong>Immune System Benefits of Olive Leaf Extract</strong>\r\n\r\nResearch suggests that olive leaf extract is a potent fighter against disease. In fact, the herb is highly prized by many natural medicine experts for its ability to boost a weakened immune system. More specifically, olive leaf extract has the ability to act as a natural pathogen killer, which includes bacteria, viruses, parasites, fungi and others.\r\n\r\nOlive leaf extract fosters the body''s overall immune system, which is continually confronted by bacteria and other microscopic substances. These bacteria and substances, invisible foreign particles that attack the body, are in the air, in our food, and on what we touch. They can filter into our systems through our ears, noses, mouths and eyes. Olive leaf extract used on a daily basis can help ward off viruses, and help build a strong immune system.\r\n\r\nThe active ingredient in olive leaf extract is oleuropein, which is a chemical product derived from the bark, roots, leaves and fruit of the olive tree. Oleuropein is what helps to ward off damage caused by insects and other outside contaminants. In addition, the olive leaf extract is an aid for offering nutritional value for detoxification in the cells during stressful periods.\r\n\r\n<strong>Antioxidant Benefits of Olive Leaf Extract</strong>\r\n\r\nThis herbal wonder also harbors antioxidant properties that help protect the body from the continuous onslaught of free radicals. Antioxidants neutralize free radicals, which are highly reactive chemical substances that can cause cellular damage within the body if left unchecked. Oleuropein can also be utilized as an antioxidant that can aid in the prevention of the oxidation process of LDL cholesterol, the more harmful one that can damage artery walls. The Mediterranean diet includes olive oil on the daily list because of the beneficial aid in lowering the susceptibility to heart disease.\r\n\r\nPhysicians have reported that chronic fatigue and fibromyalgia sufferers are often helped by olive leaf extract. People with these conditions have reported that olive leaf extract boosted their energy, lifted their sprits, and provided them with a stronger sense of well-being within one month of taking olive leaf extract supplements.', 'Olive Leaf Extract — An Ancient Cure!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'olive-leaf-extract-an-ancient-cure', '', '', '2011-02-25 17:55:08', '2011-02-25 17:55:08', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=109', 0, 'post', '', 0),
