(140, 1, '2011-02-25 13:01:46', '2011-02-25 13:01:46', 'Black walnuts are a rich source of nutritionally important ingredients. They have significant amounts of magnesium and potassium. They contain essential Omega-3 and Omega 6 fatty acids that are particularly beneficial to the heart. Having a handful of walnuts everyday can promote heart health and reduce the chances of heart attack and stroke. Studies have shown that eating walnuts can lower high cholesterol levels.\r\n\r\nIntake of black walnuts positively affects the arteries as they decrease the inflammation and reduce the level of substances that block the arteries. They aid in enhancing the circulation of blood throughout the body. Since black walnuts have omega-3 fatty acids, they also help to treat several conditions like asthma, high blood pressure and even cancer. People suffering from heartburn have also found relief by including black walnuts in their diet. A study revealed that black walnuts can kill candida, which is a yeast-like fungus. They are even better than most anti-fungal drugs.\r\n\r\nExternal application of black walnuts is also useful in the treatment of skin conditions like psoriasis and canker sores. They can successfully heal skin problems that occur due to fungal infections. Some doctors also recommend taking walnut extracts internally for disorders like rheumatism, gout, glandular disturbances, and those that occur due to parasites. When taken internally, the extract oxygenates the blood thereby destroying the parasites.', 'BLACK WALNUT —  Miracle in a nutshell!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '73-revision-7', '', '', '2011-02-25 13:01:46', '2011-02-25 13:01:46', '', 73, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/73-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2011-02-25 13:29:06', '2011-02-25 13:29:06', '<em>Makes 12 squares or 12 muffins</em>\r\n\r\n2 cups spelt flour\r\n1 cup white flour\r\n3 extra-ripe bananas, mashed\r\n1/2 cup canned pumpkin (or applesauce)\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\ndash cayenne\r\n2 Tbsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n2 tsp orange zest\r\n1 large orange, juiced (about 1/4 cup)\r\n2-3 Tbsp canola oil\r\n1/2 cup coconut milk (or preferred ''plant milk'' for lower fat)\r\n1/3 cup pumpkin seeds\r\n1 tsp salt (omit if using salted nuts/seeds)\r\n1/3 cup agave or maple syrup\r\n1/2 cup crushed pecans/nuts (optional)\r\n1/4 cup dried cranberries (optional)\r\n2 tbsp crushed/whole flax seeds (optional)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\n*Preheat oven to 375-400 degrees*\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Add flour, dry spices, salt and baking powder to a large mixing bowl. Stir well.</li>\r\n	<li>Add in the soy or coconut milk, oil, vanilla extract, bananas, pumpkin or applesauce, orange juice and maple syrup. Stir well.</li>\r\n	<li>Fold in pumpkin seeds, 1 tsp of the orange zest, and additional nuts and/or dried fruit like cranberries. If you add in lots of dried extras, you may want to increase the liquid by a few Tbsp.</li>\r\n	<li>Lay a sheet of parchment paper over a shallow 8 x 14" baking pan/dish (for bars) or line muffin tin.</li>\r\n	<li>Pour batter into baking dish.</li>\r\n	<li>Over top the batter sprinkle pumpkin seeds, cinnamon, the other tsp of orange zest.</li>\r\n	<li>Bake for 15-20 minutes depending on how thick your bars/muffins are.</li>\r\n	<li>Remove. Cool. Serve!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nBananas are rich in potassium and fiber. Nuts and seeds are rich in fiber, healthy fats, protein and vitamins. Pumpkins are rich in vitamin A and fiber.\r\n\r\nBON APPETITE!', 'Pumpkin Spice Orange Banana Bread (or muffins)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '79-revision-6', '', '', '2011-02-25 13:29:06', '2011-02-25 13:29:06', '', 79, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/79-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(142, 1, '2011-02-25 13:57:12', '2011-02-25 13:57:12', '<strong>Pumpkin Spice Orange Banana Bread (or muffins)</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Makes 12 squares or 12 muffins</em>\r\n\r\n2 cups spelt flour\r\n1 cup white flour\r\n3 extra-ripe bananas, mashed\r\n1/2 cup canned pumpkin (or applesauce)\r\n1 tsp cinnamon\r\ndash cayenne\r\n2 Tbsp baking powder\r\n1 tsp vanilla extract\r\n2 tsp orange zest\r\n1 large orange, juiced (about 1/4 cup)\r\n2-3 Tbsp canola oil\r\n1/2 cup coconut milk (or preferred ''plant milk'' for lower fat)\r\n1/3 cup pumpkin seeds\r\n1 tsp salt (omit if using salted nuts/seeds)\r\n1/3 cup agave or maple syrup\r\n1/2 cup crushed pecans/nuts (optional)\r\n1/4 cup dried cranberries (optional)\r\n2 tbsp crushed/whole flax seeds (optional)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\n*Preheat oven to 375-400 degrees*\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Add flour, dry spices, salt and baking powder to a large mixing bowl. Stir well.</li>\r\n	<li>Add in the soy or coconut milk, oil, vanilla extract, bananas, pumpkin or applesauce, orange juice and maple syrup. Stir well.</li>\r\n	<li>Fold in pumpkin seeds, 1 tsp of the orange zest, and additional nuts and/or dried fruit like cranberries. If you add in lots of dried extras, you may want to increase the liquid by a few Tbsp.</li>\r\n	<li>Lay a sheet of parchment paper over a shallow 8 x 14" baking pan/dish (for bars) or line muffin tin.</li>\r\n	<li>Pour batter into baking dish.</li>\r\n	<li>Over top the batter sprinkle pumpkin seeds, cinnamon, the other tsp of orange zest.</li>\r\n	<li>Bake for 15-20 minutes depending on how thick your bars/muffins are.</li>\r\n	<li>Remove. Cool. Serve!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nBananas are rich in potassium and fiber. Nuts and seeds are rich in fiber, healthy fats, protein and vitamins. Pumpkins are rich in vitamin A and fiber.\r\n\r\nBON APPETITE!', 'Recipe for Healthy Digestion', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '79-revision-7', '', '', '2011-02-25 13:57:12', '2011-02-25 13:57:12', '', 79, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/79-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
