(185, 1, '2011-04-26 15:31:58', '2011-04-26 15:31:58', '<strong><img class="alignright" title="Eggplant" src="http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Eggplant.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="166" />Preparation time</strong>: 1 hour 20 minutes\n\n<strong>Serves</strong>: 4 people\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\n\n2 large eggplants (approximately 3 lbs.)\n\n1/3 cup Virgin Coconut oil\n\n4 cloves of garlic, minced\n\n4 tbsp fresh parsley, finely chopped\n\n¼ cup Parmesan cheese, grated\n\nPinch sea salt and fresh ground pepper\n\n2 medium yellow onions, sliced\n\n15 oz. fresh tomato, red ripe, chopped\n\n1 cup whole milk yoghurt\n\n2 tbsp fresh dill, finely chopped\n\n2 tbsp chives, shipped\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\n\nSlice eggplants into ¾ inch rounds. Lay in a colander and sprinkle with salt. Allow to rest for 30 minutes. Rinse lightly and pat dry. While the eggplant is resting, heat a heavy bottom pan over medium heat; add just enough coconut oil to lightly coat the bottom. Add onions and cook stirring occasionally. Remove the onions to a plate. Preheat oven to 400ºF. Add enough coconut oil in a baking pan and place the eggplant slices. Bake them for 30 minutes in the oven, turning until golden brown. Heat a little more coconut oil in a pan and sauté the garlic for a few minutes. Add the tomatoes and simmer on low heat for 15 minutes Season with salt and pepper. Reserving half the parsley, stir together the yoghurt, herbs and season to taste. Pour half of the tomato sauce on top of the baked eggplants followed by onions and tomato mixture again and finish off with the yoghurt sauce. Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake for another 20 minutes. Scatter remaining parsley on top\n\nwhen cooked.\n\n<strong>Eggplant is high in fiber, potassium and B Vitamins. Many of the health </strong>\n\n<strong>benefits of eggplant come from its dark purple skin. Eggplant contains lots of antioxidants that help protect your cells from free radical damage, and also helps lower your risk for coronary heart disease.</strong>\n\n<strong>Bon Appétit</strong>\n<div><strong>\n</strong></div>', 'Recipe for a Healthy Heart - Baked Herbed Eggplant', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '160-revision-3', '', '', '2011-04-26 15:31:58', '2011-04-26 15:31:58', '', 160, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/160-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
