(268, 1, '2011-10-28 16:15:34', '2011-10-28 16:15:34', '<strong>Probiotics has been one of the hottest trends of good-to-eat foods in the recent years. However, if you are confused with terms like probiotics and prebiotics, you are not the only one!</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically probiotics are “good bacteria” that help maintain the natural balance of organisms (microflora) in the intestines. They help us combat infection, inhibit the growth of disease- producing micro-organisms, promote good digestion and boost immune function. They occur naturally in foods like yoghurt and fermented foods, added to foods, or available as supplements. The normal human digestive tract contains about 400 types of probiotic bacteria that reduce the growth of harmful bacteria and promote a healthy digestive system. The largest group of probiotic bacteria in the intestine are species that produce lactic acid, of which <em>Lactobacillus acidophilus</em>, found in yogurt, is the best known.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why the need for Probiotics supplementation?</strong>\r\n\r\nA polluted environment, processed foods, chlorinated water, and heavy use of antibiotics and other medications can destroy the friendly microflora in our bodies and allow the undesirable bacteria to multiply. The imbalance of good to bad bacteria makes the body susceptible to intestinal toxicity, bloating, constipation, poor absorption of nutrients, yeast infection and other diseases.\r\n\r\nProbiotics have been used as a form of treatment for a variety of gastrointestinal diseases including irritable bowel, lactose intolerance, traveler’s diarrhea, and antibiotic induced diarrhea.  While scientific understanding of probiotics and their potential for preventing and treating health conditions is moving ahead, here are some uses of probiotics for which there is some encouraging evidence from several studies.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Daily digestive support</li>\r\n	<li>Help treat diarrhea or constipation</li>\r\n	<li>Help prevent and treat infections of the urinary tract or female genital tract</li>\r\n	<li>Help treat irritable bowel syndrome</li>\r\n	<li>Help shorten how long an intestinal infection lasts that is caused by a bacterium called <em>Clostridium difficile</em></li>\r\n	<li>Help<strong> </strong>prevent  and treat “traveler’s diarrhea”</li>\r\n	<li>Help prevent and treat pouchitis (a condition that can follow surgery to remove the colon)</li>\r\n	<li>Help prevent and manage atopic dermatitis (eczema) in children</li>\r\n	<li>Help reduce recurrence of bladder cancer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSome experts believe probiotics to be more essential to human health than multivitamins – and there is much evidence to suggest that this could be true. Daily consumption of a well-studied strain(s) of probiotics is a simple and cost-effective way to protect your overall health from the ravages of the 21<sup>st</sup> century.', 'What are Probiotics?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '227-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-28 16:15:34', '2011-10-28 16:15:34', '', 227, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/227-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
