(358, 1, '2012-02-28 19:17:55', '2012-02-28 19:17:55', 'Few people have heard of krill oil and are probably unaware of the extraordinary benefits of this all-natural product. Krill are tiny 1-6cm long shrimp-like creatures. They live on phytoplankton and are eaten by whales, seals, penguins, squid and other fish. They are primarily fished in the Southern Ocean around Antarctica. The oil is extracted and used as a natural health supplement. It is usually taken in capsule form, similar to fish oil supplements.\r\n\r\nSeveral studies attest to the effectiveness of krill oil in managing chronic inflammation and arthritis. Notable among these studies is a paper published in the “Journal of the American College of Nutrition,” which investigated the therapeutic effects of Krill Oil on inflammation and osteoarthritis.\r\n\r\nA seven-day long krill oil treatment decreased inflammation among subjects by more than 19%, whereas the placebo group experienced a 16% increase in the levels of inflammatory C-reactive proteins. Reduction in pain, stiffness, and functional impairment was also seen among the krill oil users. On the third week of treatment, krill oil users reported reduction in inflammation by almost 30%, whereas inflammation among the placebo group worsened by more than 32%.\r\n\r\nThe researchers therefore concluded that taking only 300 mg of krill oil a day could dramatically alleviate inflammation and arthritic symptoms in as little as a week or two.', 'Treating Inflammation and Arthritis Symptoms with Krill Oil', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'treating-inflammation-and-arthritis-symptoms-with-krill-oil', '', '', '2012-02-29 17:26:29', '2012-02-29 17:26:29', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=358', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(360, 1, '2012-02-28 19:08:18', '2012-02-28 19:08:18', '<strong>Servings:</strong> 4\r\n\r\n<strong>Preparation Time:</strong> 30 min\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n1 medium onion, finely chopped\r\n2 cups homemade chicken stock or water\r\n1/2 cup rice, soaked overnight or at least a few hours\r\n2 cups plain yogurt\r\nSalt and pepper\r\n1 egg\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\nJuice from half a lemon\r\n2 tablespoons dried mint, crushed\r\n\r\n<strong>Preparation</strong>\r\nSautée the onion in the butter until soft and golden. Add the stock and simmer until just below boiling point. Add the drained rice and cook until tender, add seasoning.\r\nBeat the egg lightly, add it to the yoghurt and blend together well, then add a little warm stock to the yoghurt and mix it. Pour yoghurt slowly into the stock, and stir over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with few drops of lemon juice and garnish with mint.\r\n\r\n<strong>Nutritional information</strong> (per serving)\r\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Calcium:</td>\r\n<td valign="top">100 mg</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Vitamin D:</td>\r\n<td valign="top">20 IU</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Healthy Recipes - Yoghurt Soup', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'healthy-recipes-yoghurt-soup', '', '', '2012-02-29 17:26:29', '2012-02-29 17:26:29', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=360', 0, 'post', '', 0),
