(535, 1, '2012-10-31 14:28:51', '2012-10-31 14:28:51', 'The cold days of winter can bring on the worst of moods for even the most optimistic of people. Certain foods and supplements can restore balance to the body and provide essential nutrients, uplifting mood from inside out. The known health benefits of probiotics are numerous. They are most commonly used to help alleviate digestive disorders, but that’s just the beginning. The beneficial bacteria have also been positively linked to lower cholesterol, prevention of allergies, liver disease, yeast infections and cancer. They also help to reduce stress and improve your mood.\r\n\r\nIn a recent study, human subjects were given a probiotic formulation every day for 30 days. The probiotic regimen alleviated psychological distress in all subjects. Researchers concluded: “Exposure to chronic stress could disrupt the balance of intestinal microbiota and induce various diseases. Therefore, whatever the stress level, daily intake of probiotics could prevent such an imbalance, and the improvement in symptoms among subjects with low to mild stress levels suggests the value of prophylactic intake of probiotics in terms of digestive comfort and general well-being.”\r\n\r\nStart Taking a Probiotic Today!\r\n\r\nIf you’re looking to improve your mood naturally, in addition to aiding your digestive system among other health benefits, consider trying a probiotic dietary supplement. Look for products that contain live cultures of the most common strains of gut-friendly bacteria: Lactobacillus acidophilus, Bifidobacterium longum and Bifidobacterium bifidum. Any reputable probiotic product must have published human clinical research to support its use, and the product label must identify the bacterial strains in the product.', 'Probiotics to the rescue!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'probiotics-to-the-rescue', '', '', '2012-10-31 14:49:19', '2012-10-31 14:49:19', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=535', 0, 'post', '', 0),
