(591, 1, '2013-02-25 00:42:32', '2013-02-25 00:42:32', 'Krill are tiny 1-6cm long shrimp-like creatures. They live on phytoplankton and are eaten by whales, seals, penguins, squid and other fish. They are primarily fished in the Southern Ocean around Antarctica. The oil is extracted and used as a natural health supplement. It is usually taken in capsule form, similar to fish oil supplements.\r\n\r\nSeveral studies attest to the effectiveness of krill oil in managing chronic inflammation and arthritis. Notable among these studies is a paper published in the “Journal of the American College of Nutrition,” which investigated the therapeutic effects of Krill Oil on inflammation and osteoarthritis. A seven-day long krill oil treatment decreased inflammation among subjects by more than 19%, whereas the placebo group experienced a 16% increase in the levels of inflammatory C-reactive proteins.\r\n\r\nReduction in pain, stiffness, and functional impairment was also seen among the krill oil users. On the third week of treatment, krill oil users reported reduction in inflammation by almost 30%, whereas inflammation among the placebo group worsened by more than 32%. The researchers therefore concluded that taking only 300 mg of krill oil a day could dramatically alleviate inflammation and arthritic symptoms in as little as a week or two.', 'Treating Inflammation and Arthritis Symptoms with KRILL OIL', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'treating-inflammation-and-arthritis-symptoms-with-krill-oil-2', '', '', '2013-02-25 00:51:08', '2013-02-25 00:51:08', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=591', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(593, 1, '2013-02-25 00:46:04', '2013-02-25 00:46:04', 'Recipe for Healthy Bones\r\n\r\nServes: 4 people\r\nPreparation Time: 30 min\r\n\r\nIngredients:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 medium onion, finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>2 cups homemade chicken stock or water</li>\r\n	<li>1/2 cup rice, soaked overnight or at least</li>\r\n	<li>a few hours</li>\r\n	<li>2 cups plain yogurt</li>\r\n	<li>Salt and pepper</li>\r\n	<li>1 egg</li>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons butter</li>\r\n	<li>Juice from half a lemon</li>\r\n	<li>2 tablespoons dried mint, crushed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDirections:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sautée the onion in the butter until soft and golden.</li>\r\n	<li>Add the stock and simmer until just below boiling point.</li>\r\n	<li>Add the drained rice and cook until tender, add seasoning.</li>\r\n	<li>Beat the egg lightly, add it to the yogurt and blend together well, then add a little warm stock to the yogurt and mix it.</li>\r\n	<li>Pour yogurt slowly into the stock, and stir over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with few drops of lemon juice and garnish with mint.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNutritional information (per serving)\r\n\r\nCalcium: 100 mg\r\nVitamin D: 20 IU\r\n\r\nBon Appétit!', 'Rice Soup with Yogurt', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rice-soup-with-yogurt', '', '', '2013-02-25 00:50:42', '2013-02-25 00:50:42', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=593', 0, 'post', '', 0),
