uch as Scrabble or Sudoku. However, just like\nmuscles adapt to the repeated bouts of the same exercise, the brain also adapts. So keep\nit varied and always try new things.\n<h2>4. Quality sleep</h2>\nYour brain needs regular, restful sleep in order to function at optimum capacity. Sleep\ndeprivation not only leaves you cranky and tired, but impairs your ability to think,\nproblem-solve, and process, store, and recall information. Going to bed and getting up\nat the same time reinforces your natural circadian rhythms. Your brain’s clock responds\nto regularity.\n<h2>5. Stress management</h2>\nStress takes a heavy toll on the brain, leading to shrinkage in a key memory area of the\nbrain known as the hippocampus, hampering nerve cell growth, and increasing your risk\nof Alzheimer’s disease and dementia. Stress alters your breathing rate and impacts\noxygen levels in the brain. Keeping stress under control requires regular effort. Schedule\ndaily relaxation activities and make relaxation a priority, whether it’s a walk in the park,\nplaytime with your dog, yoga, or a soothing bath.\n<h2>6. An active social life</h2>\nStudies have shown that staying socially active may protect against Alzheimer’s disease\nand dementia, so make your social life a priority. Oftentimes, we become more isolated\nas we get older, but there are many ways to keep your support system strong and develop\nnew relationships by volunteering, joining a club or a social group or by taking group\nlessons. Commit to spending quality time with others on a regular basis.', 'The 6 pillars of a brain-healthy lifestyle', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '618-revision', '', '', '2013-06-09 23:02:04', '2013-06-09 23:02:04', '', 618, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/618-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(621, 1, '2013-06-09 23:07:53', '2013-06-09 23:07:53', 'PQQ (pyrroloquinoline quinone) is a type of B vitamin, essential for overall health. It is probably the newest of B vitamins discovered since the late 1940s. Vitamins, by definition, are essential to our health, and must be obtained from the diet since we cannot make them ourselves.\r\n\r\nSeveral studies suggest that PQQ may have potent antioxidant and anti inflammatory properties, effectively protecting nerve cells from damage and death. PQQ also enhances the biosynthesis of nerve growth factor (NGF), a key protein involved in the growth and survival of nerve cells.\r\n\r\nIn human studies on cognition, PQQ has been shown to improve various aspects\r\ncritical to mental functioning, including attention, information identification,\r\nprocessing ability, short-term memory and spatial awareness. Proper sleep is also\r\ncritical for mental health, and PQQ has been shown to improve sleep onset,\r\nmaintenance and duration, as well as reduce sleepiness on waking.', 'PQQ helps improve memory and concentration', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pqq-helps-improve-memory-and-concentration', '', '', '2013-06-11 03:47:24', '2013-06-11 03:47:24', '', 0, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/?p=621', 0, 'post', '', 0),
