(637, 1, '2013-06-11 03:53:19', '2013-06-11 03:53:19', '<h2>Question:</h2>\r\nI’m studying to be a Holistic Nutritionist and looking for ways to enhance my learning and retention. Do you have anything in your new Brain line that would help me excel in my schooling?\r\n<h2>Dr. Know:</h2>\r\nWhen Innovite launched the Brain line, we were targeting an aging population, in which cognitive function declines, and the risk of dementia/Alzheimer’s becomes more a reality. However, an increasing number of people, such as yourself, are looking to Innovite to help enhance normal cognitive function in their younger years.\r\n\r\nThis is amazing because Innovite has some very strong products to support cognitive function in a younger group. The first and most exciting, is PQQ. I’ve had my eye on this for a while, but was never able to procure the ingredient for Innovite. Finally, I’ve broken through the stalemate, and this new product will now form one of the pillars of Innovite’s new Brain/Cognitive Health line.\r\n\r\nStudies have found that it effectively protects nerve cells from damage and death, and enhances the production of nerve growth factor (NGF, a key protein involved in the growth and survival of nerve cells). This will help with the brain’s plasticity by building new connections (called synapses) between brain cells, which is important in learning. Human clinical trials have shown PQQ improves attention, processing ability, and short-term memory, among other benefits.\r\n\r\nHuman studies show that PQQ’s benefits are further enhanced when taken with CoQ10, so for those looking to realize the absolute full potential of PQQ, I would recommend Inno-Q-Nol UltraSorb (solubilized ubiquinol), which is the most absorbable CoQ10 formulation on the market (yes, even greater than other ubiquinol products).\r\n\r\nAnother great nutrient would be Acetyl-L-Carnitine. This is the only form of Lcarnitine that can cross the blood-brain barrier, and once it does, it helps power the brain’s high energy demand, and boosts the formation of acetylcholine (the neurotransmitter responsible for memory).\r\n\r\nBacopa is another great product used for centuries in traditional medicine for cognition. Modern scientific researched has confirmed its traditional uses, and Bacopa has been shown in clinical studies to improve memory and recall, reduce anxiety and energize the mind. In other studies, it has shown to be an excellent antioxidant by stimulating the brain to produce all three of the “primary antioxidants”—glutathione peroxidase, superoxide dismutase, and catalase—critical in keeping the brain as young as possible, for as long as possible.\r\n\r\nLastly, a good night’s sleep is critical to cognitive function, so if you’ve got troubles sleeping, consider Melatonin, which has not only been shown to be highly effective in promoting restful sleep, but clinical studies have shown it can also improve memory. So you’ve got lots of options—feel free to experiment and find the product (or combination) that’s right for you.\r\n\r\nYou can send questions to Lee Know at dr.Know@innovitehealth.com.', 'Expert Advice: Brain Health', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '624-autosave', '', '', '2013-06-11 03:53:19', '2013-06-11 03:53:19', '', 624, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/624-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
