(513, 1, '2012-08-23 20:08:27', '2012-08-23 20:08:27', 'Although CoQ10 has originally been thought of as a nutrient benefiting heart health, recent studies are showing huge promise in the field of fertility.  CoQ10 is currently getting press in the fertility world as a way to improve fertility in both men and women. Interest has focused mainly on older women or women with poor egg quality. CoQ10 may also help improve sperm count, but more studies are needed.\r\n\r\nMany fertility clinics are now using and encouraging their patients to take CoQ10 in an effort to improve egg quality.  A study reported in the September 2009 issue of "Fertility and Sterility" by researchers from the Toronto Centre for Advanced Reproductive Technology looked at the role of CoQ10 in improving egg quality. Lead author Eliezer Burstein, M.D., a Reproductive Endocrinology Fellow, concluded that CoQ10 supplementation increased the number of eggs ovulated. Research presented last year at the Canadian Fertility and Andrology Society also indicated that CoQ10 may play a role in female fertility – especially for middle-aged women who wish to conceive.\r\n\r\nConsider supplementation with CoQ10 if you are planning to start a family, but consult your healthcare provider first to decide the amount and the form required to fit in your specific needs.', 'CoQ10: The Next Fertility Super Supplement?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '505-revision-2', '', '', '2012-08-23 20:08:27', '2012-08-23 20:08:27', '', 505, 'http://www.inno-vite.com/articles/505-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
